# Ref: https://github.com/github/gitignore/tree/main/Global

# This is for system, tool, or editor files that may show up in any project,
# but are not directly related to that project; i.e. another developer using a
# different system, editor, & tools would not necessarily need to ignore them.

# A build/ directory would be ignored globally if created by an editor; ignored
# inside the repo if created by a checked-in build script or standard tool.

# I suggest using the above link to create your own, rather than copying this.
# It is specific to the systems and editors I use, and tuned based on frequency
# of use.

# Controversial/likely to behave unexpectedly ones first:
## Backup
*.bak
*.gho
*.ori
*.orig
*.tmp

## Log and archive files:
*.log
*.tgz

